Standards-Version: 3.5.8

Package: mkat
Architecture: all
Depends: debconf (>=0.5), mkisofs, cdrecord, cdparanoia, cd-discid, liblockfile1
Suggests: autofs
Conflicts: burn
Description: Burn, catalog, search data, audio CDs or directories
 mkat is a set of command line tools to burn and/or catalog audio, data CDs
 and arbitrary directories then search the catalog database, e.g. check 
 whether you have a certain file or audio CD in your collection. Tags can 
 be used to categorize CDs, e.g. comedy, drama, kids, sports.
 .
 Options can be passed to the programs doing the real work: cdrecord,
 mkisofs, grep. The catalog database consists of plain text files.
